<item>
            <title>[SPR-6180] Upgrade Apache HttpClient to version 4.0</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6180</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Folks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please consider upgrading HttpClient to version 4.0 which is the latest stable (GA) version of the library. Commons HttpClient 3.1 is very likely to be deprecated / officially declared end of life very soon (3 - 6 months). There have been no bug fixes in the 3.x branch for over a year. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch attached. Unfortunately I was unable to fix the Ivy build which I am not very familiar with.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oleg &lt;/p&gt;</description>
